Application: Operation to execute in MongoDB. This Application is capable to perform basic operations (insert,get,delete) in Database using command line. 

cd ~/CommandLineTool/
~/CommandLineTool$ source venv/bin/activate


------------------------------------------------------------
Please provide values to do Operations in DB
For Example (INSERT)- filename -o insert -u Kunal -l Mumbai
For Example (GET)   - filename -o get -u Kunal/-l Mumbai -f username/location/username,location
For Example (DELETE) -filename -o delete -u Kunal / -l Mumbai
-------------------------------------------------------------

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -o Operation_to_execute
                        Choose value from given list only ['insert','get','delete']
  -u username           Enter Data, For Example: -u Kunal
  -l location           Enter Data, For Example: -l Mumbai
  -f fields             Enter Fields you want to get in your output, For Example: -f username / location (optional parameter)


Used MongoDB as Database layer
Fields in Document - ID, username, location

